  "prompt": "What is the salary of an assistant professor with a PhD in India?",
  "response": "The salary of an assistant professor in India varies depending on factors like institution type, location, and experience. However, here's a general overview:\n\n1. Government/Government-recognized institutions:\n- Under the 7th Pay Commission\n- Basic salary range: \u20b957,700 - \u20b91,82,400 per month\n- With additional allowances, total compensation can be \u20b970,000 - \u20b92,00,000 per month\n\n2. Private institutions:\n- Salary range: \u20b930,000 - \u20b91,00,000 per month\n- Varies significantly based on institution reputation and location\n\n3. Central Universities:\n- Starting salary around \u20b957,700 per month\n- Can increase with academic performance and experience\n\n4. UGC (University Grants Commission) scale:\n- Entry-level assistant professors typically start at Pay Level 10\n- Salary depends on academic qualifications and pay matrix\n\nExact figures can differ based on:\n- Institution type (Central/State/Private)\n- Location\n- Individual qualifications\n- Research experience\n- Performance\n- Specific discipline\n\nThese figures are approximate and can change over time. It's best to check current job listings or contact specific institutions for the most up-to-date information.",
